hopobject.body: Do you know each other? erythritol safety dogs These small acts of resistance came to an end in October 1941, when Saint Marc joined the military academy at St Cyr. The following June he failed his exams miserably and determined to flee to Spain and, from there, join Free French forces. On July 13 1943 he was with 15 others being smuggled out of Perpignan towards the border when the lorry in which they were travelling was brought to a halt by a German patrol and its clandestine passengers were arrested.
